1
00:00:06,389 --> 00:00:08,711
I can't meet them then. I'm in court.
我那会儿不能见他们.我要出庭.

2
00:00:09,141 --> 00:00:10,260
You're in court the next day.
你在那之后第二天才出庭.

3
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:10,780
Right. 
是的.

4
00:00:11,301 --> 00:00:12,618
But I'm also in court on Wednesday.
但我周三也要出庭.

5
00:00:13,291 --> 00:00:14,705
The next day is Wednesday.
第二天就是周三.

6
00:00:15,735 --> 00:00:19,100
Trish, we just started and we're already out of sync.
Trish,我们才刚开始就已经节奏不同了.

7
00:00:19,421 --> 00:00:21,058
I cannot have all these meetings.
我不能参加所有会议.

8
00:00:21,240 --> 00:00:22,620
There aren't enough hours in the day.
白天没那么多时间.

9
00:00:23,030 --> 00:00:24,157
With all due respect, 
恕我直言,

10
00:00:24,393 --> 00:00:25,968
you don't write things down in the calendar.
你不把事情写在日程表上.

11
00:00:26,090 --> 00:00:27,780
So I don't know how full your schedule is,
所以我不知道你的安排究竟有多满,

12
00:00:27,914 --> 00:00:30,568
which is why we still have these little meetings.
这就是我们还会有这些小会的原因.

13
00:00:31,449 --> 00:00:34,173
Can we agree that the day after Wednesday is Thursday?
我们是否能一致同意周三之后是周四呢?

14
00:00:36,572 --> 00:00:38,828
That's a joke, Trish. A little joke.
开个玩笑,Trish.一个小玩笑.

15
00:00:39,468 --> 00:00:40,867
May we start from the beginning?
我们可以从头开始吗?

16
00:00:41,450 --> 00:00:42,308
By all means.
当然可以.

17
00:00:42,807 --> 00:00:46,160
The Credit Card Association would like to meet with you on Tuesday morning.
信用卡协会想在周二上午见你.

18
00:00:46,904 --> 00:00:48,735
Fine. I can do it in the morning.
好的.可以在早上进行.

19
00:00:49,073 --> 00:00:50,314
Afterwards, I'm in court.
然后我要出庭.

20
00:00:50,746 --> 00:00:51,643
Fine. Which case?
好的.哪个案子?

21
00:00:51,874 --> 00:00:53,167
People vs Kenton.
公众对Kenton.

22
00:00:53,440 --> 00:00:55,453
That case doesn't start until next week!
这案子要到下周才开始.

23
00:00:55,725 --> 00:00:57,170
We're talking about next week!
我们谈的就是下周的安排!

24
00:00:57,362 --> 00:00:58,238
We're talking about this week!
我们谈的是本周的安排!

25
00:00:58,725 --> 00:01:01,486
Trish, I said, "Let's talk about next week."
Trish,我说了,"让我们谈下周的安排."

26
00:01:02,185 --> 00:01:03,384
You said it on Friday.
你是在上周五说的.

27
00:01:03,661 --> 00:01:06,835
Last week, "next week" means "this week" this week.
上周说的"下周"到这周就变成"这周"了.

28
00:01:09,520 --> 00:01:11,213
You're going to make a very good attorney.
你会成为一名出色的律师.

